<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFEECF2DFF7FFA1A89EBFA5D" authority="Habeeb, 1958" authorityName="Habeeb" authorityYear="1958" box="[151,502,1414,1441]" class="Arachnida" family="Protziidae" genus="Pseudowandesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFEECF2DFF7FFA1A894EFA5D" box="[151,339,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Pseudowandesia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2B497C80FFEECF2DFEB2FA1A89EBFA5D" author="Habeeb, H." box="[346,502,1414,1441]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref72075" refString="Habeeb, H. (1958) New mites from New Brunswick. Leaflets of Acadian Biology, 18, 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1958">Habeeb, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
syn. nov.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F670171FFEECF2DFF7FFA368917F8F6" blockId="38.[151,1437,1414,1802]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
The two species described below bridge the gap previously assumed to separate the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFEECF2DFB08FA368D81FA39" authorityName="Habeeb" authorityYear="1958" box="[1248,1436,1451,1477]" class="Arachnida" family="Protziidae" genus="Pseudowandesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFEECF2DFB08FA368D81FA39" box="[1248,1436,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Pseudowandesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(with dish-like, unstalked Ac, see 
<bibRefCitation id="2B497C80FFEECF2DFDF0FA528AB2FA15" author="Habeeb, H." box="[536,687,1486,1513]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref72075" refString="Habeeb, H. (1958) New mites from New Brunswick. Leaflets of Acadian Biology, 18, 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1958">Habeeb 1958</bibRefCitation>
) from 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFEECF2DFD16FA528B77FA15" authorityName="Schechtel" authorityYear="1912" box="[766,874,1487,1513]" class="Arachnida" family="Protziidae" genus="Wandesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFEECF2DFD16FA528B77FA15" box="[766,874,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Wandesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="669F6018FFEECF2DFC9AFA4D8BB8FA16" box="[882,933,1488,1514]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(with cupuliform Ac on stalks). Ac of water mites are plesiotypically located on a basal sclerite which may be reduced to a fine, nearly invisible ring, in other cases fused to surrounding sclerite plates, or extended to a cylindrical stalk which elevates the Ac over the idiosoma surface. As generally observed in other hydryphantid subfamilies, the length of such stalks differs species-specifically also in 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFEECF2DFEC3F9C2898AF985" authorityName="Schechtel" authorityYear="1912" box="[299,407,1631,1657]" class="Arachnida" family="Protziidae" genus="Wandesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFEECF2DFEC3F9C2898AF985" box="[299,407,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Wandesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All intermediate situations are possible between nearly invisible (absent?) stalks (species previously attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFEECF2DFE43F91E8A7AF961" authorityName="Habeeb" authorityYear="1958" box="[427,615,1667,1693]" class="Arachnida" family="Protziidae" genus="Pseudowandesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFEECF2DFE43F91E8A7AF961" box="[427,615,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Pseudowandesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), rather short stalks (the species described here from 
<collectingCountry id="37CF41E1FFEECF2DFB3BF91E8D42F962" box="[1235,1375,1667,1694]" name="Madagascar" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
), and stalks elongated to a various degree (species previously attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFEECF2DFC41F93A8C08F93D" authorityName="Schechtel" authorityYear="1912" box="[937,1045,1703,1729]" class="Arachnida" family="Protziidae" genus="Wandesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFEECF2DFC41F93A8C08F93D" box="[937,1045,1703,1729]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Wandesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="669F6018FFEECF2DFBF6F9358C49F93E" box="[1054,1108,1704,1730]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). This character is obviously not suitable for grouping species in the genus, and 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFEECF2DFD0BF9568B82F919" authorityName="Habeeb" authorityYear="1958" box="[739,927,1739,1765]" class="Arachnida" family="Protziidae" genus="Pseudowandesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFEECF2DFD0BF9568B82F919" box="[739,927,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Pseudowandesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is therefore considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFEECF2DFF7FF972891EF8F5" authorityName="Schechtel" authorityYear="1912" box="[151,259,1775,1801]" class="Arachnida" family="Protziidae" genus="Wandesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFEECF2DFF7FF972891EF8F5" box="[151,259,1775,1801]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Wandesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
